# Biogrix Feature Modules

## Structure

Backend API must be organized by **feature modules**. Each module is self-contained.

## Module Structure

Each module must contain:

- `controller` — HTTP request handling
- `service` — Business logic
- `routes` — Endpoint mappings
- `validation` — Input validation (optional)
- `repository` or data layer — Data access (optional)

## Example Modules

- customers
- plants
- gas-usage
- billing
- payments
- complaints
- maintenance
- reports

## Folder Structure Example

```
backend/api/
└── src/
    └── modules/
        ├── customers/
        │   ├── customers.controller.js
        │   ├── customers.service.js
        │   └── customers.routes.js
        ├── plants/
        │   ├── plants.controller.js
        │   ├── plants.service.js
        │   └── plants.routes.js
        └── billing/
            ├── billing.controller.js
            ├── billing.service.js
            └── billing.routes.js
```

## Layer Responsibilities

- **Controllers** — Handle HTTP requests and responses; parse input; call services
- **Services** — Contain all business logic; call database/repository
- **Routes** — Map endpoints to controller methods only

## Rules

- Controllers must remain **thin** (no business logic)
- Business logic must live in **services**
- Controllers call services; services perform operations
- Each module must not import from other modules directly; use shared code when cross-module logic is needed
